@startuml
title Optimisation Cancellation Flow

skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 2
skinparam roundcorner 10
skinparam sequenceParticipantBackgroundColor #EEF2FF
skinparam sequenceParticipantBorderColor #4F46E5
skinparam sequenceActorBackgroundColor #EEF2FF
skinparam sequenceActorBorderColor #4F46E5
skinparam noteBorderColor #A5B4FC
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #EEF2FF

actor "User & OEX " as Caller
participant "OGW" as OGW
participant "OSB MS" as OSB
participant "NGW" as NGW
participant "OC MS" as OCMS
database "OC MS DB" as OCDB
queue "OC MS Outbox" as Outbox
queue "Kafka" as Kafka
participant "Python/Gurobi\nWorker" as Worker

note over Caller,OGW
  External access is authenticated at OGW.
  OGW validates the caller token/session and establishes caller identity,
  tenant, roles/scopes, correlation id, and trace context.
end note

note over OGW,OSB
  OGW forwards user identity, tenant, roles/scopes, correlation id,
  and trace context only to OSB MS.
  OSB MS performs user-context authorisation before the request crosses NGW.
end note

note over NGW,OCMS
  Service-to-service calls use mTLS.
  User context terminates at NGW.
  Downstream services see only the calling system/service identity,
  internal route policy, correlation id, and trace context.
end note

== Cancellation Request ==

Caller -> OGW : 1. POST /optimisation/{id}/cancellation\n(If-Match header)
OGW -> OGW : 2. Authenticate caller\nValidate token/session\nDerive identity, tenant, roles/scopes
OGW -> OSB : 3. Invoke OSB MS\nForward user identity/claims, correlation id, trace context
OSB -> OSB : 4. Validate user context & runtime state\nAuthorise cancellation action\nExpose cancellation action only if allowed
OSB -> NGW : 5. Forward cancellation request\nPreserve If-Match, system caller identity, correlation id, trace context\nDo not forward user context downstream
NGW -> NGW : 6. Enforce internal route policy\nTerminate user context\nUse system/service identity for downstream call
NGW -> OCMS : 7. Route cancellation request\n(mTLS, service/system auth context only)

== Validation ==

OCMS -> OCDB : 8. Validate ETag (If-Match)
OCDB --> OCMS : ETag confirmed
OCMS -> OCMS : 9. Authorise service/system caller\nDo not perform end-user authorisation\nUser-context authorisation already completed in OSB MS
OCMS -> OCDB : 10. Check lifecycleStatus is\nACKNOWLEDGED, QUEUED, or PROCESSING
OCDB --> OCMS : Status eligible for cancellation

== State Transition & Event Publishing ==

OCMS -> OCDB : 11. Update lifecycleStatus = CANCELLING
OCDB --> OCMS : Confirmed
OCMS -> Outbox : 12. Write OptimisationRequestedEvent\n(instruction = CANCEL) — same transaction
note right of Outbox
  Outbox write is part of the OC MS durable state change.
  Event publication is idempotent and carries correlation/trace context.
end note
Outbox -> Kafka : 13. Relay publishes event to Kafka

== Worker Cancellation ==

Kafka -> Worker : 14. Consume CANCEL instruction
Worker -> Worker : 15. Stop, cancel, or safely ignore\nwork where possible

== Final Projection ==

Worker -> Kafka : 16. Publish cancellation outcome event
Kafka -> OCMS : 17. Consume outcome
OCMS -> OCDB : 18. Project lifecycleStatus = CANCELLED\nwhen cancellation confirmed or safely resolved

note right of OCDB
  Final state is eventual —
  worker determines safe resolution.
end note

@enduml
